headline: MINNESOTA TEAMSTERS UNANIMOUSLY AUTHORIZE STRIKE AT SYSCO
summary: Teamsters at Sysco Minnesota have voted unanimously to authorize a strike if the company fails to deliver a fair contract. The group of over 230 drivers and warehouse workers are demanding wage increases, stronger benefits, and improved working conditions.

headline: Sysco (SYY) Completes Buyback, Reports Earnings Drop and Predicts Future Sales Growth
summary: Sysco (SYY) recently updated its share buyback program, completing a significant repurchase, and reported fiscal year-end earnings that showed increased sales but a decline in net income and EPS. The company's corporate guidance for a 3% to 5% growth in fiscal 2026 sales also added context to their strategic direction. During a quarter with a 9.78% increase in share price, this likely aligned with broader market optimism around corporate earnings, as evidenced by similar trends in the S&P 500...
